    "name": "Mesh Convergence Study — Non-cannulated Pedicle Screw FEA",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was performed on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model. Four mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine, extra-fine) were evaluated by monitoring von Mises stress at the screw-rod junction and construct stiffness QoI. Richardson extrapolation was applied to estimate the discretization error. The study confirmed that the medium mesh density achieves a grid convergence index (GCI) below 2% for all QoIs, satisfying the discretization error acceptance criterion.",
