    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted given that the COU is explicitly limited to static compression-bending under ASTM F1717 and no dynamic claims are made. All three primary QoIs satisfy the pre-established quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percentage difference < 10%). The FEA model ensemble is judged credible for the stated COU.",
